snippet.textDisplay: I have nothing against “body positivity” until it begins to kill you. Obesity in the United States is a huge problem that kills thousands of people per year. It in no way should be widely accepted in society. And it is in no way natural. As you get fatter, fat lard begins to build up around vital organs, specifically the heart. What this means is that as fat is added around that area more weight is being subjected to your heart, making the process of pumping blood throughout your body unnecessarily difficult. This can obviously make you more prone to heart attacks. Not to mention that you’re more likely to get a disease like Diabetes. Besides health risks, there are also economic issues. The US spends $190.2 Billion Dollars Every Year towards medical treatment related to obesity. That makes up a whopping 21% of the US’s medical spending, almost a quarter of it in total. People need to realize that being fat is in no way an okay or natural thing. It is very much deadly and very selfish, as you are costing everyone around you in taxpayer money. Lizzo should drop the cheetos and lose some weight before she croaks at 40.
